      <akn:section eId="sec_7_1531_18">
        <akn:num>7-1531.18</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Law governing validity; choice of law as to execution of document of gift; presumption of validity.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_7-1531_18_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A document of gift is valid if executed in accordance with:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_7-1531_18_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>If a document of gift is valid under this section, the law of the District of Columbia governs the interpretation of the document of gift.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_7-1531_18_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A person may presume that a document of gift or amendment of an anatomical gift is valid unless that person knows that it was not validly executed or was revoked.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
